---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '2026-03-27';
---
<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service" description="Omnigram Terms of Service">
  <div class="py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-invert prose-slate">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-10">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the Omnigram application and related services
        ("Service") provided by the Omnigram project ("we", "us", or "our"). By using the Service,
        you agree to these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">1. Description of Service</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        Omnigram is an open-source, self-hosted book library and reading application.
        The Service includes the Omnigram mobile/desktop application and the Omnigram server software.
        You are responsible for hosting and maintaining your own server instance.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">2. Open Source License</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        Omnigram is released under the <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">MIT License</a>.
        You are free to use, modify, and distribute the software in accordance with the license terms.
        The full license text is available in the
        <a href="https://github.com/lxpio/omnigram" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">source code repository</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">3. User Responsibilities</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">By using the Service, you agree to:</p>
      <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-2 mt-3">
        <li>Comply with all applicable laws and regulations</li>
        <li>Ensure you have the right to store and read the content you import</li>
        <li>Maintain the security of your self-hosted server</li>
        <li>Not use the Service for any unlawful purpose</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">4. Content</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        You retain all rights to the content you import into Omnigram. We do not claim ownership
        of your books, annotations, or any other content. Since data is stored on your own server,
        you are solely responsible for your content and its legality.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">5. AI Features</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        Omnigram's AI features are optional and require you to configure your own AI provider.
        Your use of third-party AI services (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, etc.) is governed by
        their respective terms of service. We are not responsible for how third-party AI providers
        handle the data you send to them.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">6. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND,
        EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. WE DO NOT WARRANT THAT THE SERVICE WILL BE UNINTERRUPTED,
        SECURE, OR ERROR-FREE. USE OF THE SERVICE IS AT YOUR OWN RISK.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, WE SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT,
        INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO
        LOSS OF DATA, LOSS OF PROFITS, OR BUSINESS INTERRUPTION, ARISING FROM YOUR USE OF THE SERVICE.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">8. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        The Service may integrate with third-party services (AI providers, WebDAV, OPDS).
        We are not responsible for the availability, accuracy, or content of these external services.
        Your use of third-party services is at your own risk and subject to their respective terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">9. Changes to Terms</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page
        with an updated revision date. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes
        acceptance of the modified Terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-10 mb-4">10. Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
        For questions about these Terms, please contact us:
      </p>
      <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-2 mt-3">
        <li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/lxpio/omnigram/issues" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">github.com/lxpio/omnigram/issues</a></li>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:omnigram@lxpio.com" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">omnigram@lxpio.com</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
